scenes.description: Mori Calliope walks through a virtual sculpture garden, reflecting on friends who are no longer active in the community.
Calliope shakes off the sentimental mood and begins moving to a new section of the world.
Calliope announces that this virtual world will be released to the public in the coming days.
Calliope runs across a vast body of water toward a distant desert area.
Calliope reaches the 'Ame Desert' and investigates a large clock buried in the sand.
A dimensional door is discovered, leading Calliope through a space-like void.
Calliope arrives at a recreation of the original desert bus stop and enters a museum dedicated to HoloMyth's first year.
